fields.title: Borsch
fields.description:
• Prep:20 mins
  • Cook:2 hrs

Make a warming bowl of borsch (also known as borscht or borshch) with this simple and comforting recipe. Serve this hearty soup with a dollop of soured cream and a chunk of crusty bread
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

For the stock:

  • 1kg fatty beef shin, (left in large chunks)
  • 1 onion, peeled and left whole
  • 1 bay leaf

For the broth:

  • 2.2kg potatoes, peeled and chopped
  • 2 tbsp sunflower oil
  • 1 onion, finely diced
  • 1 carrot, roughly grated
  • 200g beetroot, peeled and chopped into matchsticks
  • 1 red pepper, chopped (optional)
  • ½ x 400g can chopped tomatoes
  • 6 prunes, pitted (we used French Agen prunes)
  • ½ white cabbage, shredded
  • 400g can red kidney beans, drained and rinsed
  • 100ml soured cream or crème fraîche, to serve
  • ½ bunch dill, chopped
  • crusty bread, to serve
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    To make the stock, put the meat, whole onion, bay leaf and 2 litres of lightly salted cold water in a large saucepan. Cook over a very low heat for 1 hr 30 mins or until the beef shin is soft and falls apart easily – this can take up to 3 hrs. Skim off the scum with a spoon from time to time. Break up any larger pieces of beef into the broth, remove the whole onion and discard.

  • STEP 2

    Add the potatoes to the borscht, season well with salt and pepper and cook for 10-15 mins until tender. Meanwhile, heat the sunflower oil in a large, deep frying pan. Add the diced onion and carrot, and cook over a medium heat, stirring, until the carrot is soft and is about to start caramelising.

  • STEP 3

    Add the beetroot and cook for around 5 mins, stirring occasionally. Add the red pepper, if using, and cook for another 2 mins, then add the tomatoes and prunes, stir, then increase the heat and boil to reduce slightly, before adding everything to the borscht.

  • STEP 4

    Add the shredded cabbage and the kidney beans, and cook for 7-10 mins or until tender. Serve with a dollop of sour cream or crème fraîche, lots of chopped dill and some crusty bread.

fields.title: Varenuku
fields.description:
• Prep:45 mins
  • Cook:30 mins

Variations on these delicious dumplings are found all over Eastern Europe. Olia's are filled with tangy sauerkraut, crunchy cabbage and crispy shallots
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

For the filling:

  • 1 tbsp sunflower oil
  • 2 shallots, finely chopped
  • 150g sauerkraut, finely chopped
  • 150g hispi (sweetheart) cabbage, shredded

For the dough

  • 1 large egg, lightly beaten
  • ½ tbsp vegetable oil
  • 350g plain flour, plus extra for dusting

For the crispy shallots:

  • vegetable oil, for frying
  • 2 shallots, finely sliced
  • plain flour, for dusting

To serve:

  • 45g butter
  • 60ml soured cream
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    First, make the crispy shallots. Heat the oil in a saucepan to 180C (a cube of bread will turn golden in 15 secs). Toss the shallots in a little flour and deep-fry for 1 min or until light golden and crispy. Drain on kitchen paper. Can be made up to two days before and kept in an airtight container.

  • STEP 2

    To make the filling, heat the oil in a medium non-stick frying pan and gently fry the shallots for 10 mins until starting to turn golden.

  • STEP 3

    Add the sauerkraut and cabbage, and cook for 5-10 mins until the cabbage has softened. Taste and add a little salt if under-seasoned, or sugar if stringent. Scrape into a bowl and leave to cool completely.

  • STEP 4

    To make the dough, mix the eggs and oil with 125ml water, then gradually add in the flour, mixing well with your hands. Knead it on a well-floured surface until the dough stops sticking to your hands. You should end up with firm, elastic dough. Wrap it in cling film and rest in the fridge for at least 30 mins, or overnight.

  • STEP 5

    Flour your work surface generously. Roll out the dough to a 40cm circle or until the dough is as thick as £1 coin.

  • STEP 6

    Using a 9cm cookie cutter, cut out discs in the dough – you should end up with about 25 discs. Do not throw away the off-cuts – we throw them in with the pierogi when boiling to minimise any waste.

  • STEP 7

    Have a well-floured tray ready. Put 1 tsp of the filling into the centre of each disc. In your hand, fold in half around the filling and seal to create half-moon shapes. Put them on the floured tray, making sure they don’t touch each other.

  • STEP 8

    Bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil and carefully lower the pierogi in. Boil them for 2 mins or until they float to the top.

  • STEP 9

    Drain and serve with a knob of butter and some soured cream. Finish by sprinkling the crispy shallots on top to serve.

fields.title: Golubci
fields.description:
• Prep:20 mins
  • Cook:1 hr

Add this vegan dish to your repertoire. We've filled cabbage leaves with satisfying brown rice and lentils along with mint, lemon, tahini and pine nuts
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 16 large Savoy cabbage leaves, stems trimmed (430g prepared weight)
  • 1 tbsp rapeseed oil
  • 2 large onions (360g), finely chopped
  • 40g pine nuts
  • 1 tbsp ground cumin
  • 1 tbsp ground coriander
  • 1 ½ tsp cinnamon
  • 150g brown basmati rice
  • 1 ½ tbsp vegetable bouillon powder
  • 390g can green lentils, drained
  • 1 lemon, zested and juiced
  • 4 tbsp chopped mint
  • 2 tbsp tahini
  • 1 garlic clove, finely grated

For the salad:

  • 6 tomatoes, sliced
  • ¼ cucumber (150g), sliced
  • 12 Kalamata olives, pitted and sliced
  • 1 tbsp chopped mint
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Bring a large pan of water to the boil, add the cabbage leaves and put a heavy ladle on top to keep them submerged. Boil for 4 mins, then drain, reserving the water.

  • STEP 2

    Meanwhile, heat the oil in a non-stick pan. Reserve 2 tbsp of the onion, then fry the rest for 10 mins until just golden. Stir in the pine nuts and cook until starting to colour. Add the spices and rice, then pour in 450ml of the reserved water. Stir in the bouillon powder, cover and cook for 15 mins until the rice is almost tender and the liquid is absorbed. Stir in the lentils, zest and mint.

  • STEP 3

    Heat the oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Put a spoonful of the rice into the centre of a cabbage leaf, roll up and put in a shallow casserole dish. Repeat with the remaining rice and leaves. Cover and bake for 30 mins until the rice is fully tender.

  • STEP 4

    Meanwhile, combine the tahini, lemon juice, garlic and 3 tbsp water, and mix the salad ingredients with the reserved onion. If you're following our Healthy Diet Plan, serve half the rolls with half of the sauce and half of the salad. Cover and chill the rest to eat another day. Will keep in the fridge for two to three days. Reheat in the microwave until hot.

fields.title: BBQ chicken platter
fields.description:
• Prep:40 mins
  • Cook:1 hr and 10 mins

Roast or barbecue these BBQ chicken pieces then serve on a platter with onion rings, coleslaw and mac ‘n’ cheese for an all-American banquet
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients

  • 1 whole chicken, jointed, or 8 bone-in chicken pieces (we used legs, breasts, thighs and wings)

For the spice rub

  • 1 tsp sea salt
  • 1 tbsp smoked paprika
  • 1 tsp garlic granules

For the BBQ sauce

  • 2 tbsp runny honey
  • 2 tbsp cider vinegar
  • 2 tbsp light brown soft sugar
  • 200g American mustard
fields.cooking_method:
Method

  • STEP 1

    To make the spice rub, mix the salt, smoked paprika and garlic granules together in a large bowl. Add the chicken pieces and toss well to coat. Transfer to the fridge to chill for at least 2 hrs.

  • STEP 2

    To make the BBQ sauce, tip the honey, vinegar, sugar and mustard into a pan and bring to the boil, stirring to dissolve the sugar. Remove from the heat and leave to cool.

  • STEP 3

    Heat the oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Pour half of the the BBQ sauce into a large bowl, add the seasoned chicken pieces and toss to coat. Spread the chicken out on a baking tray and roast for 1 hr, occasionally basting with more BBQ sauce, until the chicken is cooked through and sticky. Serve with truffled mac ‘n’ cheese, onion rings and coleslaw if you like.

fields.title: American pancakes
fields.description:
• Prep:25 mins
  • Cook:30 mins

Easy, American-style, fluffy pancakes are great for feeding a crowd at breakfast or brunch. Top with something sweet like fruit, jam or syrup, or rashers of crispy bacon.
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 200g self-raising flour

  • 1 ½ tsp baking powder
  • 1 tbsp golden caster sugar
  • 3 large eggs
  • 25g melted butter, plus extra for cooking
  • 200ml milk
  • vegetable oil, for cooking

To serve:

  • maple syrup
  • toppings of your choice, such as cooked bacon, chocolate chips, blueberries or peanut butter and jam
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Mix 200g self-raising flour, 1 ½ tsp baking powder, 1 tbsp golden caster sugar and a pinch of salt together in a large bowl.

  • STEP 2

    Create a well in the centre with the back of your spoon then add 3 large eggs, 25g melted butter and 200ml milk.

  • STEP 3

    Whisk together either with a balloon whisk or electric hand beaters until smooth then pour into a jug.

  • STEP 4

    Heat a small knob of butter and 1 tsp of oil in a large, non-stick frying pan over a medium heat. When the butter looks frothy, pour in rounds of the batter, approximately 8cm wide. Make sure you don’t put the pancakes too close together as they will spread during cooking. Cook the pancakes on one side for about 1-2 mins or until lots of tiny bubbles start to appear and pop on the surface. Flip the pancakes over and cook for a further minute on the other side. Repeat until all the batter is used up.

  • STEP 5

    Serve your pancakes stacked up on a plate with a drizzle of maple syrup and any of your favourite toppings.

fields.title: Corndogs
fields.description:
• Prep:20 mins
  • Cook:15 mins

Make American-inspired corndogs by coating frankfurter sausages in a cornmeal batter, then deep-frying and serving with ketchup and yellow mustard
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 100ml cornmeal
  • 100g plain flour
  • 1 egg, lightly beaten
  • 1 tsp caster sugar
  • ½ tsp fine sea salt
  • 1 tbsp baking powder
  • 150ml whole milk
  • 8 frankfurters
  • vegetable oil, for deep-frying
  • ketchup and American mustard, to serve
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Tip the cornmeal, flour, egg, caster sugar, salt, baking powder and milk into a bowl, and whisk until you have a smooth, lump-free batter. Carefully pour the batter into a tall jug or glass.

  • STEP 2

    Push a wooden skewer through the length of each frankfurter, so it goes about three-quarters of the way through. Fill a pan no more than a third full with oil and heat to 180C, or until a cube of bread dropped in browns within 30 seconds.

  • STEP 3

    Working with one frankfurter at a time, submerge it into the batter and gently turn to coat – it should be completely covered. Carefully drop into the oil and fry for 2-3 mins, or until the batter is crisp and golden. Drain on a sheet of kitchen paper. Repeat with the remaining frankfurters. Serve with ketchup and American mustard for dipping or drizzling over.

fields.title: Lionhead meatball soup
fields.description:
• Prep:20 mins
  • Cook:20 mins

Enjoy these Shanghai-style mini 'lionhead' meatballs in a rich, earthy and sweet broth made with Chinese leaf and dried shiitake mushrooms
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 100ml groundnut oil, for frying

For the meatballs

  • 500g lean pork mince
  • 4 garlic cloves, finely minced
  • 2 tbsp grated ginger
  • 2 spring onions, finely chopped
  • 1 pinch of ground white pepper
  • 50ml shaoxing rice wine or dry sherry
  • 1 tbsp dark soy sauce
  • 2 tbsp light soy sauce
  • 1 tbsp toasted sesame oil
  • 1 egg, beaten
  • 1 tbsp cornflour

For the soup broth:

  • 500ml vegetable stock
  • 5 dried Chinese mushrooms slices
  • 200g Chinese leaf, washed, quartered lengthways from leaf to stem
  • 1 tbsp light soy sauce
  • 1 tbsp toasted sesame oil
  • 1 pinch of ground white pepper
  • 1 tbsp cornflour, mixed with 1 tbsp water
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Put all the ingredients for the meatballs into a large bowl and stir to combine well. Using wetted hands, take a golf ball-sized mound and roll into a round shape. Put on a plate and repeat to make 12.

  • STEP 2

    Pour the groundnut oil into a large wok or pan and set over high heat until a thermometer reads 160C. Put a meatball onto a slotted spoon and gently lower into the oil. Leave to brown for 5-7 mins until golden, then cook all the meatballs. To check if a meatball is cooked, push a skewer through and, if it comes out clean, it’s cooked. Lift the meatballs out, then drain on a plate lined with kitchen paper and set aside.

  • STEP 3

    Add 1 tbsp of the hot oil to a clean wok. Put over a high heat, add the vegetable stock, 850ml water, the mushrooms and Chinese leaf, and cook over a medium heat for 10-12 mins. Add the meatballs and cook for a further 4-5 mins, adjusting the cabbage leaves so they wrap around each meatball – the meatball resembles the ‘lion's head’ and the cabbage resembles the ‘mane’. Season with sesame oil, salt and ground white pepper. To thicken the soup, add 1 tbsp of the cornflour mixture when the broth is boiling. Then turn the heat to low and garnish with the sliced spring onions.

  • STEP 4

    Ladle a portion into soup bowls, spoon a meatball and with some Chinese leaf and sliced mushrooms, and serve immediately.

fields.title: Honey, sesame & orange king prawns
fields.description:
• Prep:10 mins
  • Cook:10 mins

Enjoy our honey, sesame and orange king prawns as part of a Chinese feast the whole family will love. Top with spring onions and serve with rice
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 2 tsp sesame oil
  • 1 large orange, zested and juiced
  • 3 tbsp honey
  • 2 tbsp low-salt soy sauce
  • 1 tbsp rice vinegar
  • 3 tbsp cornflour
  • 2 tbsp sesame seeds
  • generous pinch of Chinese five-spice powder
  • 300g raw king prawns
  • 3 tbsp sunflower or vegetable oil
  • 1 garlic clove, thinly sliced
  • 2 spring onions, sliced
  • 200g long-grain rice, cooked, to serve
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Mix the oil, orange zest and juice, honey, soy and vinegar in a bowl, then combine the cornflour, sesame seeds, five-spice and a pinch of salt in another bowl. Run a small knife down the back of each prawn, so they butterfly out as they cook, helping more sauce stick to them.

  • STEP 2

    Toss the prawns through the cornflour mixture. Heat the oil in a large wok or frying pan. When it’s very hot, add the garlic. Sizzle for 10 secs, but don’t let it brown. Add the prawns and any flour and seeds left in the bowl. Stir-fry over a high heat for a few minutes, until the prawns are pink and the sesame seeds are golden. Tip the prawns onto a plate and pour the sauce mixture into the wok. Bubble for a few minutes until thickened. Add the prawns back to the wok and stir to coat in the sauce. Heat through for another 30 seconds. Top with spring onions and serve with rice.

fields.title: Chow mein
fields.description:
• Prep:10 mins
  • Cook:20 mins
    • plus marinating

A classic Chinese dish of stir-fried egg noodles with shredded chicken breast. Experiment with different fish, meat or vegetables
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 225g dried or fresh egg noodles
  • 1 tbsp sesame oil, plus 1 tsp
  • 100g boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into fine shreds
  • 2½ tbsp groundnut oil
  • 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped
  • 50g mangetout, finely shredded
  • 50g prosciutto or cooked ham, finely shredded
  • 2 tsp light soy sauce
  • 2 tsp dark soy sauce
  • 1 tbsp Shaohsing rice wine or dry sherry
  • ½ tsp freshly ground white pepper
  • ½ tsp golden caster sugar
  • 2 spring onions, finely chopped

For the marinade:

  • 2 tsp light soy sauce
  • 2 tsp Shaoxing rice wine or dry Sherry
  • 1 tsp sesame oil
  • ½ tsp freshly ground white pepper
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Cook 225g egg noodles in a large pan of boiling water for 3-5 mins, then drain and put them in cold water. Drain thoroughly, toss them with 1 tbsp sesame oil and set aside.

  • STEP 2

    Combine 100g chicken breasts, cut into fine shreds, with 2 tsp light soy sauce, 2 tsp Shaohsing rice wine or dry sherry, 1 tsp sesame oil, ½ tsp white pepper and ½ tsp salt for the marinade, mix well and then leave to marinate for about 10 mins.

  • STEP 3

    Heat a wok over a high heat. Add 1 tbsp groundnut oil and, when it is very hot and slightly smoking, add the chicken shreds.

  • STEP 4

    Stir-fry for about 2 mins and then transfer to a plate.

  • STEP 5

    Wipe the wok clean, reheat until it is very hot then add 1½ tbsp groundnut oil.

  • STEP 6

    When the oil is slightly smoking, add the 2 finely chopped garlic cloves and stir-fry for 10 seconds.

  • STEP 7

    Add 50g finely shredded mangetout and 50g finely shredded prosciutto, and stir-fry for about 1 min.

  • STEP 8

    Add the noodles, 2 tsp light soy sauce, 2 tsp dark soy sauce,1 tbsp Shaohsing rice wine or dry sherry, ½ tsp white pepper, ½ tsp golden caster sugar, 2 finely chopped spring onions and 1 tsp salt.

  • STEP 9

    Stir-fry for 2 mins. Return the chicken and any juices to the noodle mixture. Stir-fry for about 3-4 mins or until the chicken is cooked.

  • STEP 10

    Add 1 tsp sesame oil and give the mixture a few final stirs. Put on a warm platter and serve immediately.

fields.title: Pasta alla norma
fields.description:
• Prep:10 mins
  • Cook:1 hr
    • plus draining

Try this easy version of an alla norma, which uses roast aubergine instead of fried. It's then tossed with spaghetti and a rich tomato and basil sauce
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 2 aubergines, cut into 3cm chunks
  • 1 heaped tsp salt
  • 4 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
  • 1 small onion, finely chopped
  • 2 garlic cloves, crushed
  • pinch chilli flakes
  • 2 x 400g tins chopped tomatoes
  • 1 tsp sugar
  • 350g spaghetti (egg-free, if needed)
  • small bunch basil, shredded, plus a few leaves to serve
  • 1 heaped tbsp capers
  • ricotta salata or parmesan, finely grated, to serve (optional)
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Toss the aubergines with the salt, then tip into a colander set over a bowl for 30 mins, to extract any moisture.

  • STEP 2

    Heat 2 tbsp of the oil in a casserole dish or saucepan. Tip in the onion and a pinch of salt, and cook over a low heat for 10 mins. Add the garlic and chilli, and cook for 1 min. Tip in the tomatoes and sugar, and bring to the simmer. Cook, uncovered, for 20 mins, stirring occasionally. Heat the oven to 220C/200C fan/gas 7.

  • STEP 3

    Pat the aubergine dry with kitchen paper, then toss with the remaining oil. Spread out on a baking sheet and roast for 25-30 mins until softened and golden around the edges. Meanwhile, cook the pasta following pack instructions, reserving 100ml of the cooking water.

  • STEP 4

    Stir the aubergine into the sauce with the basil and capers. Season to taste, then toss the spaghetti in the pan with the sauce and a splash of the pasta water. Divide between four bowls and top with the ricotta and extra basil, if using.

fields.title: Iced hazelnut zabagliones
fields.description:
• Prep:25 mins
  • Cook:5 mins

An indulgent but refreshing Italian-style dessert
fields.ingredients:
Ingredients:

  • 100g bag hazelnut, toasted
  • 400ml double cream
  • 85g golden caster sugar, plus 1 tbsp
  • 3 egg yolks
  • 5 tbsp sweet marsala

For the coffee marsala sauce:

  • 4 tbsp chocolate hazelnut spread
  • 2 tbsp sweet marsala
  • 2 tsp instant coffee dissolved in 2 tbsp boiling water
fields.cooking_method:
Method:

  • STEP 1

    Put all sauce ingredients into a small pan, bring to the boil, whisking, then let it cool completely to a silky, thickened sauce.

  • STEP 2

    Whizz all but 1 tbsp of the nuts in a small food processor until fine. Very roughly chop the rest, then set aside. Softly whip the cream with 1 tbsp sugar. Put the rest of the sugar into a pan, add 100ml water, then slowly heat until the sugar has dissolved. Turn up the heat, boil for 1 min, then take off the heat.

  • STEP 3

    Line two individual pudding basins or ramekins with cling film. Put the egg yolks and Marsala into a large bowl over a pan of hot water, then whisk until it starts to thicken and get foamy. Keep the beaters running and trickle the sugar syrup into the mix. Keep beating for about 5 mins until the mixture is thick and holds a trail. Take off the heat, then whisk until cooled. Add the cream, whisk again, then fold in the ground nuts with a metal spoon.

  • STEP 4

    Ripple half the sauce through the mix, spoon into the moulds, then fold the cling film over. Freeze the remaining mix in a tub or make more individual puds, if you like. Freeze for at least 4 hrs or overnight to set.

  • STEP 5

    Turn onto plates, then let ices sit for 10 mins to soften a little. Scatter over the chopped nuts, then pour a little sauce over to serve.

fields.title: Mini Burgers
fields.description: If you’re looking to go the extra mile and make hamburger buns from scratch, try out this recipe! It’s easy and the results are impressive. After the buns come out of the oven, we brush them with melted butter to make them even more delicious. We turned these into mini buns, but if you want to make regular-sizes buns, just divide the dough into 8 equal portions and bake for 15–18 minutes instead.
fields.ingredients:
1/2 teaspoon onion powder

1/2 teaspoon garlic powder

1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper

1/2 teaspoon kosher salt

1 pound ground chuck

8 (3-inch) buns or rolls, split in half

2 to 3 tablespoons mayonnaise
fields.cooking_method:
1. Preheat the oven to 250 degrees F. Preheat a griddle to 350 degrees F.
  2. Combine the onion powder, garlic powder, pepper, and salt in a small bowl. Set aside.
  3. Line a jellyroll or sheet pan with parchment paper, and place the ground chuck in the middle of the pan. Cover the meat with a large sheet of plastic wrap. Roll meat with a rolling pin until it covers the surface of the pan; it should be very thin. Remove the plastic wrap, and sprinkle the meat with the seasoning mixture. Fold the meat in half, from side to side, using the parchment paper. Use a pizza wheel to cut the meat into 8 even squares.
  4. Wrap the buns in foil and place in the oven for 5 to 10 minutes. Meanwhile, place the burgers on the griddle and cook for 2 to 3 minutes per side.
  5. Remove the buns from the oven. Spread a small amount of mayonnaise on each bun and top with the burger and any other condiments, as desired. Serve immediately.

fields.title: Kyiv Chicken
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 50 minutes
  • Description: This traditional Ukrainian dish features a tender chicken breast pounded and rolled with herbs and butter, then breaded and fried to a golden crisp. A classic dish that offers a delightful mix of textures and flavors.
fields.ingredients:
• 4 chicken breasts, boneless and skinless
  • 50g butter, softened
  • 2 cloves garlic, minced
  • 1 tbsp parsley, chopped
  • 100g breadcrumbs
  • 2 eggs, beaten
  • 50g flour
  • Salt and pepper to taste
fields.cooking_method:
• Flatten the chicken breasts to about 1/4 inch thickness. Mix the butter with garlic and parsley. Spread evenly on the chicken.
  • Roll the chicken breasts tightly and secure with toothpicks. Season with salt and pepper.
  • Dredge each chicken roll in flour, dip in beaten eggs, then coat in breadcrumbs.
  • Fry in a skillet over medium heat until golden and cooked through, about 7-8 minutes per side.
  • Remove toothpicks, slice and serve hot.

fields.title: Nalysnyky
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 40 minutes
  • Description: Delicate Ukrainian crepes filled with a savory mix of cheese and dill, these Nalysnyky are a delightful treat for any meal. They are typically served as an appetizer or a light main course.
fields.ingredients:
• For the crepes:
    • 1 cup all-purpose flour
    • 2 eggs
    • 1½ cups milk
    • Pinch of salt
    • Butter, for frying
  • For the filling:
    • 250g cottage cheese
    • 1 egg, beaten
    • 2 tbsp fresh dill, chopped
    • Salt and pepper to taste
fields.cooking_method:
• Combine flour, eggs, milk, and salt in a bowl. Whisk until smooth to create the crepe batter. Let rest for 20 minutes.
  • Heat a non-stick frying pan and lightly coat with butter. Pour a small amount of batter into the pan, swirling to spread evenly. Cook until golden, flip and cook the other side. Repeat with remaining batter.
  • Mix cottage cheese, beaten egg, dill, salt, and pepper for the filling.
  • Place a tablespoon of the filling onto each crepe and roll tightly.
  • Arrange filled crepes in a baking dish, cover with foil, and bake at 350°F for 20 minutes. Serve warm.

fields.title: Deruny
fields.description:
• Cooking Time: 25 minutes
  • Description: These traditional Ukrainian potato pancakes are crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, often served with a side of sour cream. A staple in Ukrainian cuisine, Deruny are perfect for any meal, offering a delicious blend of simple ingredients.
fields.ingredients:
• 6 large potatoes, peeled and grated
  • 1 onion, finely chopped
  • 2 eggs
  • 3 tablespoons all-purpose flour
  • Salt and pepper to taste
  • Vegetable oil, for frying
  • Soured cream, for serving
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Squeeze out excess moisture from the grated potatoes using a cloth. Combine the potatoes, onion, eggs, flour, salt, and pepper in a bowl.
  • Step 2: Heat oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Drop spoonfuls of the potato mixture into the pan, flatten slightly, and fry until golden brown on both sides.
  • Step 3: Drain on paper towels and serve hot with soured cream.

fields.title: Mango Sticky Rice
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 10 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 20 minutes
  • Description: A classic Thai dessert known for its simplicity and deliciousness, Mango Sticky Rice combines sweet, ripe mangoes with creamy coconut milk and sticky rice. It's a sweet, creamy dish that's both refreshing and satisfying.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 cup sticky rice
  • 1 ripe mango, sliced
  • 1 cup coconut milk
  • 1/4 cup sugar
  • 1/4 teaspoon salt
  • Toasted sesame seeds or mung beans for garnish
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Soak the sticky rice in water for at least 2 hours, then drain.
  • Step 2: Steam the rice until tender, about 15-20 minutes.
  • Step 3: While the rice is cooking, heat the coconut milk in a saucepan. Add sugar and salt, stirring until dissolved.
  • Step 4: Mix the warm rice with three-quarters of the coconut milk. Let sit to absorb the liquid for about 15 minutes.
  • Step 5: Serve the rice with mango slices, drizzle with the remaining coconut milk, and sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds or mung beans.

fields.title: Beef Stroganoff
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 15 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 30 minutes
  • Description: A rich and creamy sauce of sautéed pieces of beef served in a sauce with smetana (sour cream). Beef Stroganoff is a classic dish that has been a family favorite for generations, known for its robust and comforting flavors.
fields.ingredients:
• 500g beef sirloin, thinly sliced
  • 2 tablespoons butter
  • 1 onion, finely chopped
  • 250g mushrooms, sliced
  • 1 cup beef broth
  • 1 cup sour cream
  • 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard
  • Salt and pepper to taste
  • Chopped parsley for garnish
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat and cook the beef until browned. Remove and set aside.
  • Step 2: In the same skillet, add onions and mushrooms, cooking until softened.
  • Step 3: Return the beef to the skillet, add beef broth, and simmer for about 10 minutes.
  • Step 4: Stir in sour cream and mustard, cook gently until the sauce is hot but not boiling. Season with salt and pepper.
  • Step 5: Garnish with parsley before serving with noodles or rice.

fields.title: Pasta alla Norma
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 15 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 30 minutes
  • Description: Pasta alla Norma is a traditional Italian dish from Sicily featuring sautéed eggplant tossed with tomato sauce and topped with ricotta salata cheese. This dish combines sweet, savory, and salty flavors in a delightful harmony.
fields.ingredients:
• 400g pasta (e.g., rigatoni)
  • 1 large eggplant, cubed
  • Olive oil
  • 2 cloves garlic, minced
  • 400g canned tomatoes
  • Salt and pepper to taste
  • Basil leaves
  • Ricotta salata, grated
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Salt the cubed eggplant and let sit for 30 minutes to draw out moisture, then rinse and pat dry.
  • Step 2: Heat olive oil in a large pan, add eggplant, and fry until golden. Remove and set aside.
  • Step 3: In the same pan, add garlic and sauté briefly before adding tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
  • Step 4: Simmer the tomato sauce for 10 minutes, then return the eggplant to the pan. Cook for another 5 minutes.
  • Step 5: Cook the pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and toss with the sauce. Serve topped with grated ricotta salata and fresh basil.

fields.title: General Tso's Chicken
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 20 minutes
  • Description: General Tso's Chicken is a beloved Chinese-American dish featuring crispy fried chicken coated in a sweet, slightly spicy sauce with garlic, ginger, and chili flakes. It's a perfect blend of sweet and heat.
fields.ingredients:
• 500g boneless chicken thighs, cut into chunks
  • 2 eggs, beaten
  • 1 cup cornstarch
  • Oil for frying
  • 3 tablespoons soy sauce
  • 2 tablespoons hoisin sauce
  • 1 tablespoon vinegar
  • 1/4 cup sugar
  • 1 teaspoon minced ginger
  • 2 cloves garlic, minced
  • 1 teaspoon chili flakes
  • Green onions and sesame seeds for garnish
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Coat chicken pieces in cornstarch then dip in beaten eggs.
  • Step 2: Fry chicken in hot oil until golden and crispy. Remove and drain on paper towels.
  • Step 3: In a separate pan, mix soy sauce, hoisin sauce, vinegar, sugar, ginger, garlic, and chili flakes. Bring to a simmer.
  • Step 4: Add the fried chicken to the sauce and toss to coat evenly.
  • Step 5: Garnish with sliced green onions and sesame seeds before serving.

fields.title: Caprese Salad
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 10 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 0 minutes
  • Description: Caprese Salad is a simple yet elegant Italian salad, consisting of fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, basil, and a drizzle of balsamic glaze. It's a fresh, vibrant dish perfect for any occasion.
fields.ingredients:
• 4 large ripe tomatoes, sliced
  • 300g fresh mozzarella cheese, sliced
  • Fresh basil leaves
  • Salt and pepper to taste
  • Olive oil
  • Balsamic glaze
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Arrange slices of tomatoes and mozzarella cheese alternately on a platter.
  • Step 2: Tuck fresh basil leaves between the slices.
  • Step 3: Season with salt and pepper.
  • Step 4: Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic glaze before serving.

fields.title: Texas BBQ Brisket
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 30 minutes (plus marinating)
  • Cooking Time: 8 hours
  • Description: Texas BBQ Brisket is a cornerstone of American barbecue, known for its slow-cooked, smoky flavor and tender texture. Served with BBQ sauce on the side, it's a favorite at gatherings.
fields.ingredients:
• 3 kg beef brisket
  • 3 tablespoons brown sugar
  • 3 tablespoons paprika
  • 3 tablespoons salt
  • 2 tablespoons black pepper
  • 1 tablespoon garlic powder
  • 1 tablespoon onion powder
  • 2 cups BBQ sauce
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Mix brown sugar, paprika, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder to make the rub.
  • Step 2: Apply the rub to the brisket and let marinate overnight.
  • Step 3: Slow-cook the brisket in a smoker at 225 degrees Fahrenheit for about 8 hours or until tender.
  • Step 4: Let the brisket rest before slicing. Serve with BBQ sauce on the side.

fields.title: Szechuan Beef Stir-Fry
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 15 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 10 minutes
  • Description: Szechuan Beef Stir-Fry is a fiery and flavorful dish featuring thinly sliced beef and colorful vegetables, all tossed in a bold Szechuan sauce. It's known for its spicy kick from chili peppers and Szechuan peppercorns.
fields.ingredients:
• 500g beef flank steak, thinly sliced against the grain
  • 2 bell peppers, assorted colors, sliced
  • 1 onion, sliced
  • 3 tablespoons soy sauce
  • 2 tablespoons hoisin sauce
  • 1 tablespoon chili paste
  • 1 teaspoon Szechuan peppercorns, crushed
  • 2 cloves garlic, minced
  • 1 teaspoon ginger, minced
  • 2 tablespoons vegetable oil
  • Sesame seeds and green onions for garnish
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over high heat. Add the beef and stir-fry until it starts to brown.
  • Step 2: Add garlic, ginger, and Szechuan peppercorns, cooking for another minute until fragrant.
  • Step 3: Add bell peppers and onion, continuing to stir-fry until vegetables are just tender.
  • Step 4: Stir in soy sauce, hoisin sauce, and chili paste, mixing well to coat the beef and vegetables evenly.
  • Step 5: Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, then garnish with sesame seeds and green onions before serving.

fields.title: Apple Cake (Yabluchnyk)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 40 minutes
  • Description: Yabluchnyk is a traditional Ukrainian apple cake that is delightfully moist and packed with sweet, cinnamon-scented apples. Perfect for enjoying with a cup of tea or coffee.
fields.ingredients:
• 3 cups all-purpose flour
  • 1 cup sugar
  • 1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened
  • 4 large apples, peeled, cored, and sliced
  • 2 teaspoons baking powder
  • 1 teaspoon cinnamon
  • 2 eggs
  • 1 cup milk
  • Powdered sugar for dusting
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour a baking pan.
  • Step 2: In a bowl, cream together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time.
  • Step 3: In another bowl, whisk flour, baking powder, and cinnamon. Gradually add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
  • Step 4: Pour half of the batter into the prepared pan. Layer with apple slices, then top with the remaining batter.
  • Step 5: Bake for about 40 minutes. Let cool and dust with powdered sugar before serving.

fields.title: Sorrel Soup (Green Borsch)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 40 minutes
  • Description: Green Borsch is a traditional Ukrainian sorrel soup that is tart and refreshing, typically served with hard-boiled eggs and sour cream. It's especially popular in the spring and early summer when sorrel is in season.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 bunch fresh sorrel, finely chopped
  • 2 potatoes, peeled and cubed
  • 1 carrot, diced
  • 1 onion, chopped
  • 6 cups chicken or vegetable broth
  • 2 hard-boiled eggs, chopped
  • 1/2 cup sour cream
  • Dill, chopped for garnish
  • Salt and pepper to taste
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: In a large pot, bring the broth to a boil. Add potatoes, carrot, and onion. Cook until vegetables are tender.
  • Step 2: Add the chopped sorrel to the pot and simmer for another 5 minutes.
  • Step 3: Season with salt and pepper to taste.
  • Step 4: Serve the soup hot, topped with chopped hard-boiled eggs, a dollop of sour cream, and a sprinkle of dill.

fields.title: Honey Cake (Medovik)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 30 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 60 minutes
  • Description: Medovik is a classic Ukrainian dessert featuring layers of honey-infused sponge cake filled with a creamy, slightly tangy sour cream frosting. Each layer is thin and delicate, melding beautifully with the cream for a moist and flavorful dessert.
fields.ingredients:
• 3/4 cup honey
  • 3/4 cup sugar
  • 2 teaspoons baking soda
  • 4 eggs
  • 4 cups all-purpose flour
  • 2 cups sour cream
  • 1 cup powdered sugar
  • 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: In a saucepan, combine honey, sugar, and baking soda, and heat until foamy. Let cool slightly.
  • Step 2: Beat the eggs and gradually add to the honey mixture. Then incorporate the flour to form a dough.
  • Step 3: Roll out the dough and cut into circles. Bake each layer at 350°F (175°C) for about 5-7 minutes or until golden.
  • Step 4: For the frosting, mix sour cream, powdered sugar, and vanilla until smooth.
  • Step 5: Assemble the cake by spreading frosting between each cooled cake layer. Frost the top and sides. Refrigerate overnight to set.

fields.title: Pampushky (Garlic Bread Rolls)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes (plus rising time)
  • Cooking Time: 25 minutes
  • Description: Pampushky are soft, fluffy bread rolls typically served with borscht. These rolls are unique for their aromatic garlic oil topping, which adds a delightful flavor.
fields.ingredients:
• 500g all-purpose flour
  • 1 packet dry yeast
  • 1 teaspoon sugar
  • 1 teaspoon salt
  • 300ml warm water
  • 3 tablespoons vegetable oil
  • 4 cloves garlic, minced
  • Fresh herbs, finely chopped (such as dill or parsley)
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Combine flour, yeast, sugar, and salt in a large bowl. Add warm water and mix to form a dough.
  • Step 2: Knead the dough on a floured surface until smooth. Place in a greased bowl, cover, and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
  • Step 3: Punch down the dough and shape into small rolls. Place on a baking sheet, cover, and let rise again for 30 minutes.
  • Step 4: Bake in a preheated oven at 375°F (190°C) for about 25 minutes or until golden.
  • Step 5: While baking, heat oil and sauté garlic until fragrant. Add chopped herbs.
  • Step 6: Brush the baked rolls with the garlic oil mixture while still warm.

fields.title: Syrnyk (Sweet Cheese Pancakes)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 15 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 10 minutes
  • Description: Syrnyk are thick, fluffy pancakes made from sweetened cottage cheese, making them a beloved breakfast or dessert in Ukraine. They're typically served with sour cream, jam, or fresh berries.
fields.ingredients:
• 500g cottage cheese
  • 2 eggs
  • 3 tablespoons sugar
  • 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
  • 4 tablespoons all-purpose flour
  • Extra flour for dusting
  • Butter or oil for frying
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: In a bowl, mix cottage cheese, eggs, sugar, and vanilla until smooth.
  • Step 2: Add flour to form a thick batter.
  • Step 3: Heat butter or oil in a skillet. Drop spoonfuls of the batter into the skillet, and flatten slightly.
  • Step 4: Fry over medium heat until golden on both sides, about 4-5 minutes per side.
  • Step 5: Serve warm with sour cream, jam, or fresh berries.

fields.title: Vinegret Salad
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 20 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 30 minutes
  • Description: Vinegret is a vibrant and hearty Ukrainian salad made with beets, potatoes, carrots, and pickles, dressed in sunflower oil or a light vinaigrette. This salad is known for its colorful presentation and is a staple during Ukrainian holidays and family gatherings.
fields.ingredients:
• 3 medium beets
  • 2 medium potatoes
  • 2 carrots
  • 3 pickles, diced
  • 1 small onion, finely chopped
  • 1 cup sauerkraut, drained (optional)
  • 1/2 cup cooked peas
  • 3 tablespoons sunflower oil
  • Salt and pepper to taste
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: Boil the beets, potatoes, and carrots until tender, then cool, peel, and dice into small cubes.
  • Step 2: In a large bowl, combine the diced beets, potatoes, carrots, pickles, onion, sauerkraut (if using), and peas.
  • Step 3: Drizzle with sunflower oil and season with salt and pepper. Mix well to combine all the ingredients.
  • Step 4: Refrigerate for at least an hour to allow the flavors to meld together.
  • Step 5: Serve chilled, garnished with fresh dill or parsley if desired.

fields.title: Beetroot Salad with Herring (Shuba)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 45 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 0 minutes (requires chilling)
  • Description: Shuba, also known as Herring Under a Fur Coat, is a layered salad with herring, beets, carrots, potatoes, and eggs, each layer smothered with mayonnaise. It's visually striking and deeply flavorful.
fields.ingredients:
• 200g salted herring, finely chopped
  • 3 medium beets, boiled and grated
  • 2 potatoes, boiled and grated
  • 2 carrots, boiled and grated
  • 3 hard-boiled eggs, grated
  • 1 onion, finely chopped
  • Mayonnaise for layering
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: In a deep glass dish, layer the ingredients starting with herring and then adding a thin layer of mayonnaise.
  • Step 2: Follow with layers of onion, potatoes, carrots, and beets, adding a layer of mayonnaise between each.
  • Step 3: Top with grated eggs and cover the top layer with mayonnaise.
  • Step 4: Cover and refrigerate for several hours, preferably overnight, to allow the flavors to blend.
  • Step 5: Serve chilled, cut into squares or wedges.

fields.title: Spring Salad (Zelenyj Salat)
fields.description:
• Preparation Time: 15 minutes
  • Cooking Time: 5 minutes
  • Description: Zelenyj Salat, or Green Salad, is a fresh, vibrant dish made from the first spring greens. It typically includes radishes, cucumbers, green onions, and a variety of herbs, dressed lightly with oil and vinegar.
fields.ingredients:
• 1 bunch of radishes, thinly sliced
  • 2 cucumbers, thinly sliced
  • 1 bunch of green onions, chopped
  • 1/2 cup mixed fresh herbs (dill, parsley, cilantro), chopped
  • 2 tablespoons sunflower oil
  • 1 tablespoon vinegar
  • Salt and pepper to taste
fields.cooking_method:
• Step 1: In a salad bowl, combine radishes, cucumbers, green onions, and fresh herbs.
  • Step 2: Drizzle with sunflower oil and vinegar. Toss to coat evenly.
  • Step 3: Season with salt and pepper to taste.
  • Step 4: Serve immediately to maintain the crispness of the vegetables.
